Hi Karl,
I am interested in the code. Is there any possibility
to get it?

regards
Sven

--- Karl Meredith <kvm@...> schrieb:


---------------------------------
JLK,

I have implemented a 1D spherical model in Cantera for
my own research.  It
is not incorporated into the Cantera distribution
however.  Also, it is only
in C++, not python or matlab.  It would take some
cleaning up before I'd
feel comfortable distributing it.  Let me know if you
are interested.

Karl

Subject: [cantera] Spherically Symmetric


I'm new to Cantera.  Just installed it today.  But
based on the
documentation online it does not appear that Cantera
is currently
capable of handling 1D spherically symmetric geometry.
 If this is so,
I was wondering if someone could fill me in on the
process that would
be required for me to add this feature.  What language
is the part of
the source code that contains the equations written
in?  Is there
something I can do through the Matlab toolbox to
attain the
functionality I'm looking for?

Thanks!
JLK
